# repos-manager

> A single CLI tool to clone and sync all your Git repositories from GitHub, GitLab, Forgejo, Bitbucket, and Radicle.

## What it does
repos-manager syncs Git repositories from multiple providers into a local directory structure that mirrors the remote namespace: provider/owner/repo.

## Key features
- Multi-provider: GitHub, GitLab, Forgejo/Gitea, Bitbucket, Radicle
- Parallel sync with configurable job count
- Status overview: dirty, ahead, behind, diverged repos
- Filter and ignore patterns
- Self-update mechanism
- Config file support
- Auto-generated shell sourceme files

## Install
git clone git@github.com:Dxsk/repos-manager.git && cd repos-manager && make install

## Usage
repos-manager login
repos-manager sync --all
repos-manager status

